# Gantt Chart Visualization Module

This document outlines the frontend implementation plan for the new interactive Gantt view, combining `gantt-task-react` with live TanStack/WebSocket data.

## User Review Required

> [!WARNING]  
> `gantt-task-react` natively builds custom SVG connections but applying raw red rings using raw Tailwind arbitrary classes onto native deep SVG arrays might misalign on zoom. I plan to use CSS scoped overrides mathematically matching `.gantt-task` classes instead to apply `ring-2 ring-red-500` specifically for tasks listed inside the `criticalPathTaskIds` array mapping. Please confirm you are okay with CSS class injection into the Gantt library.

## Proposed Changes

### 1. Store Setup (`frontend/src/store/ganttStore.ts`)
- Implements Zustand to synchronize global interactions.
- Will track `zoomLevel` (`ViewMode.Day | Week | Month`).
- Keeps `criticalPathTaskIds` temporarily mapped if needed manually for UI parsing outside the exact TanStack payload.

### 2. Layout Navigation (`DashboardLayout.tsx` & `App.tsx`)
- We will install `lucide-react`'s `<LayoutList>` inside `navItems`.
- We will bind it to route: `/workspaces/:workspaceId/gantt`.
*(You don't have deeply bound FrontEnd permission store methods cleanly exported matching 'dashboard:read' exclusively yet since workspaces operate off owner/member context mainly, so I will filter visually using `useWorkspaceStore` presence).*

### 3. Core View (`frontend/src/features/gantt/GanttView.tsx`)
This massive component encompasses:
- **TanStack `useQuery`**: Hooks actively to `api.get('/workspaces/${workspaceId}/gantt')`.
- **WebSocket Triggers**: Connects generic `dependency:created`, `dependency:deleted`, and `critical-path:updated`. On socket triggers, invokes `queryClient.invalidateQueries`.
- **View Modeling**: Transforms native backend array into literal `{ start, end, name, id, type, progress, dependencies }` object wrappers natively understood by `gantt-task-react`. 
- **Draggable Interactions**: Maps `onDateChange` native Gantt hooks outwards via `api.patch(`/tasks/${task.id}`)` converting UI drops to solid Postgres writes.

### 4. Dependency Interactions (`DependencyModal.tsx`)
- Triggered visually. Provides Select components utilizing standard Shadcn/Tailwind UI to allow users to draw structural dependencies (Finish-Start naturally) and POST to `/dependencies`.

## Verification Plan
1. Local bundle mapping using Vite to ensure `gantt-task-react` maps completely seamlessly through Bun's internal dependency caching logic.
2. Clicking/dragging Gantt components must trigger real API mutation wrappers.
